# ContextIO Scopes

This diagram visualizes the three ContextIO scopes (Session, Agent, Shared) and their lifecycles, access patterns, and required capabilities.

## Scope Overview

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph scopes["Context Scopes"]
        direction TB
        session["Session Scope"]
        agent["Agent Scope"]
        shared["Shared Scope"]
    end
    
    subgraph lifetimes["Lifetime"]
        direction TB
        life_session["Current Run Only"]
        life_agent["Across Runs"]
        life_shared["Persistent"]
    end
    
    subgraph access["Access Pattern"]
        direction TB
        acc_session["Single Agent"]
        acc_agent["Single Agent"]
        acc_shared["Multiple Agents"]
    end
    
    subgraph caps["Required Capability"]
        direction TB
        cap_session["MemoryRead/Write<br/>{ scope: Session }"]
        cap_agent["MemoryRead/Write<br/>{ scope: Agent }"]
        cap_shared["MemoryRead/Write<br/>{ scope: Shared }"]
    end
    
    session --> life_session --> acc_session --> cap_session
    agent --> life_agent --> acc_agent --> cap_agent
    shared --> life_shared --> acc_shared --> cap_shared
    
    style session fill:#e1f5e1,stroke:#333
    style agent fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#333
    style shared fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#333
```

## Scope Comparison Table

| Scope | Lifetime | Access | Use Case | Capability Required |
|-------|----------|--------|----------|-------------------|
| **Session** | Current run only | This Agent only | Temporary working memory | `MemoryRead { scope: Session }`<br/>`MemoryWrite { scope: Session }` |
| **Agent** | Across runs | This Agent only | Persistent agent memory | `MemoryRead { scope: Agent }`<br/>`MemoryWrite { scope: Agent }` |
| **Shared** | Across runs | Multiple Agents | Cross-agent collaboration | `MemoryRead { scope: Shared }`<br/>`MemoryWrite { scope: Shared }` |

## Key Rules

1. **Explicit Scope Required** - Implementations MUST NOT infer cross-Agent memory access from a lower-scope capability. Writing to `Shared` scope requires explicit `MemoryWrite { scope: Shared }`.

2. **No Automatic Escalation** - Having `MemoryRead { scope: Agent }` does NOT grant access to `Shared` scope.

3. **Isolation Boundaries** - Session scope is completely isolated per-run. Agent scope persists but is private to that Agent. Shared scope is the only cross-Agent channel.

## ContextIO Operations by Scope

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph ops["ContextIO Operations"]
        read["context_read"]
        write["context_write"]
        search["context_search"]
        snapshot["snapshot"]
        restore["restore"]
    end
    
    subgraph session_ops["Session Scope"]
        s_read["✓ Read"]
        s_write["✓ Write"]
        s_search["✓ Search"]
        s_snapshot["✓ Snapshot"]
        s_restore["✓ Restore"]
    end
    
    subgraph agent_ops["Agent Scope"]
        a_read["✓ Read"]
        a_write["✓ Write"]
        a_search["✓ Search"]
        a_snapshot["✓ Snapshot"]
        a_restore["✓ Restore"]
    end
    
    subgraph shared_ops["Shared Scope"]
        sh_read["✓ Read"]
        sh_write["✓ Write*"]
        sh_search["✓ Search"]
        sh_snapshot["✗ N/A"]
        sh_restore["✗ N/A"]
    end
    
    read --> s_read & a_read & sh_read
    write --> s_write & a_write & sh_write
    search --> s_search & a_search & sh_search
    snapshot --> s_snapshot & a_snapshot
    restore --> s_restore & a_restore
```

*Note: Shared scope write (`sh_write`) requires explicit `MemoryWrite { scope: Shared }` capability.

