## Implementation Notes

- **Session** data is typically stored in-memory and lost after the run completes
- **Agent** data requires persistent storage (database, file system, etc.)
- **Shared** data requires concurrent access controls and conflict resolution
- All scopes support `context_read`, `context_write`, and `context_search`
- Only Session and Agent scopes support `snapshot` and `restore` operations
